T1	Participants 342 531;532 948	STUDY DESIGN The study involved 82 overweight adults participating in the Lifestyle Intervention Treatment Evaluation (LITE) follow-up study at Oulu University Hospital in northern Finland. METHODS Psychiatric diagnostic assessments were based on the Structured Clinical Interview for DSMIV disorders (SCID-I) conducted by a clinical psychiatrist. Anhedonia (lack of pleasure) was assessed as one of the core symptoms of major depression and chronic depression (dysthymia). Anhedonia was defined to be present if the participants reported having suffered a major loss of interest during the previous month.
